The members and guests of the Club wandered hither and thither, sat, stood, met, and separated, some in uniform and some in evening dress, and a few here and there with powdered hair and in Russian kaftdns. Pow- dered footmen, in livery with buckled shoes and smart stockings, stood at every door anx- iously noting visitors' every movement in order to offer their services.
